  <refsect1>
    <title>DESCRIPTION</title>

    <para>This manual page documents briefly the
      <command>&dhpackage;</command> command.</para>

    <para>This manual page was written for the &debian; distribution
      because the original program does not have a manual page.
    </para>

    <para><command>&dhpackage;</command> helps you to visually arrange your 
       partitions. It makes use of the libparted library to accomplish that.
       Just start it from the menu.</para>

    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-?</option>
          <option>--help</option>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Show summary of options.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>--display=<replaceable>X</replaceable></option>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Specifies the X display that gparted will use.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>--installer</option>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>NOTE: You should never have to use this, this is an option
	     that is provided for UbuntuExpress and does some different
	     assumptions.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>


